Question: Prove or disprove $$I=\lim_{n\to\infty} \frac{(2^{2^n}+1)(2^{2^n}+3)(2^{2^n}+5)\cdots (2^{2^n+1}+1)}{(2^{2^n})(2^{2^n}+2)(2^{2^n}+4)\cdots (2^{2^n+1})}=\sqrt{2}$$ I know 
\begin{align}\frac{(2^{2^n}+1)(2^{2^n}+3)(2^{2^n}+5)\cdots (2^{2^n+1}+1)}{(2^{2^n})(2^{2^n}+2)(2^{2^n}+4)\cdots (2^{2^n+1})}=&\left(1+\dfrac{1}{2^{2^n}}\right)\left(1+\dfrac{1}{2^{2^n}+2}\right)\\&\cdots\left(1+\dfrac{1}{2^{
2^n+1}}\right)\end{align} so
$$\lim_{n\to\infty}\left(1+\dfrac{1}{2^{2^n}}\right)\left(1+\dfrac{1}{2^{2^n}+2}\right)\cdots\left(1+\dfrac{1}{2^{
2^n+1}}\right)=\sqrt{2}\ ?$$ I feel this result is very surprising. This problem comes from Chris's sis. and I use wolfram, limit wofl can't find it I often use this theta function and is this true? Thank you.
